## Questionnaire Domains

### 🔐 Domain 1 — Security Controls (6 questions)

| # | Question | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 1.1 | Do you enforce MFA for all users accessing systems that process our data? | MFA is the single most effective control against credential compromise |
| 1.2 | Is data encrypted in transit (TLS 1.2+) and at rest (AES-256)? | Encryption protects data confidentiality if systems are breached |
| 1.3 | How frequently do you conduct penetration testing? Who performs it? | External pen tests validate security posture independently |
| 1.4 | What is your patch management cadence for critical vulnerabilities? | Unpatched systems are the #1 attack surface for ransomware |
| 1.5 | Have you experienced a security breach in the last 3 years? If yes, describe. | Breach history indicates actual security effectiveness |
| 1.6 | Do you maintain a formal vulnerability management program? | Ongoing vuln management is required by SOC 2 and ISO 27001 |

---

### 🗄️ Domain 2 — Data Handling (4 questions)

| # | Question | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 2.1 | In which countries is our data stored and processed? | Data residency affects GDPR, HIPAA, and regulatory compliance |
| 2.2 | What is your data retention policy for customer data? | Excessive retention increases breach exposure and regulatory risk |
| 2.3 | Who within your organization can access our data? | Access minimization is a core zero-trust principle |
| 2.4 | How is our data securely deleted at contract termination? | Data not properly deleted creates long-tail breach risk |

---

### ✅ Domain 3 — Compliance Certifications (4 questions)

| # | Question | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 3.1 | Do you hold a current SOC 2 Type II report? Can you provide it? | SOC 2 Type II is the gold standard for SaaS vendor assurance |
| 3.2 | Are you ISO/IEC 27001 certified? If yes, provide certificate. | ISO 27001 demonstrates a formal ISMS is in place |
| 3.3 | If you process health data, are you HIPAA compliant? | HIPAA compliance is legally required for healthcare data |
| 3.4 | Do all employees complete annual security awareness training? | Human error is the #1 cause of breaches — training mitigates it |

---

### 🔄 Domain 4 — Business Continuity (3 questions)

| # | Question | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 4.1 | Do you have a documented and tested Business Continuity Plan? | A BCP proves the vendor can maintain service during disruptions |
| 4.2 | What are your SLA uptime commitments and historical uptime? | Uptime SLAs define vendor accountability |
| 4.3 | How frequently is your Disaster Recovery plan tested? | Untested DR plans frequently fail when actually needed |

---

### ⚖️ Domain 5 — Legal & Governance (3 questions)

| # | Question | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|
| 5.1 | Do you carry cyber liability insurance? What is the coverage limit? | Insurance provides financial recourse if the vendor causes a breach |
| 5.2 | Are you willing to sign a Data Processing Agreement (DPA)? | DPAs establish legal data handling obligations under GDPR/CCPA |
| 5.3 | Do your subcontractors and sub-processors meet the same security standards? | Fourth-party risk is an extension of third-party risk |

